      • LCUser

        public LCUser()
        Constructs a new LCUser with no data in it. A LCUser constructed in this way will not have an objectId and will not persist to the database until LCUserManager.signUp() is called.

      • getCurrentUser

        public static LCUser getCurrentUser()
        This retrieves the currently logged in LCUser with a valid session, either from memory or disk if necessary.
        Returns:
        The currently logged in LCUser.

      • logOut

        public static void logOut()
        Logs out the currently logged in user session. This will remove the session from disk, log out of linked services, and future calls to LCUser.getCurrentUser() will return null.

      • enableAutomaticUser

        public static void enableAutomaticUser()
        Enables automatic creation of anonymous users. After calling this method, LCUser.getCurrentUser() will always have a value. The user will only be created on the server once the user has been saved, or once an object with a relation to that user or an ACL that refers to the user has been saved.

      • isAuthenticated

        public boolean isAuthenticated()
        Whether the LCUser has been authenticated on this device. This will be true if the LCUser was obtained via a loginInBackground or signUp method. Only an authenticated LCUser can be saved (with altered attributes) and deleted.
        Returns:
        isAuthenticated
